25/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Russian Industry and Energy Minister Victor Hristenko said in Zagreb on Monday (June 25th) that his country is talking with Bulgaria, Greece and Serbia about a new pipeline that would carry Russian natural gas to Europe under the Black Sea. The Russian and Italian energy companies Gazprom and ENI signed a memorandum for co-operation on the project Saturday. The 900-km long pipeline could become operational in three years. 
On Friday, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov met with Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin and confirmed Sofia's interest in the project. (Darik, RIA Novosti - 25/06/07; BTA - 24/06/07)
